bq. There are many places doesn't judging LOG.isDebugEnabled() when logging debug info in DFSOutputStream and DataStreamer.

There is no need to use {{LOG.isDebugEnabled()}} when the logging is the following format (e.g. "+" is not used):
{code}
  LOG.debug("Connecting to datanode {}", dnAddr);
{code}
Please see the Logging section of  https://github.com/steveloughran/formality/blob/master/styleguide/styleguide.md for the detail., Thanks [~ajisakaa] for comments. Updating the latest patch and removing unnecessary code., Thanks [~linyiqun] for updating the patch. I'm thinking we don't need to use nested try-catch-finally clause. The code can be replaced by one try-catch-finally clause as follows:
{code}
try {
  // call some methods to flush buffer.
  // don't need to call closeThreads(false) because the threads are closed by the finally block.
} catch (ClosedChannelException ignored) {
} finally {
  // don't need to call setClosed() because closeThreads(true) calls setClosed() in the finally block.
  closeThreads(true);
}
